body_text.text:
Data was obtained from the official New York City Heath public website as it relates to the COVID-19 cases, hospitalizations and death. The data presented reflect the most recent information the health department has collected about people who have tested positive for COVID-19 in NYC. Death rate by race and ethnicity groups was most recently updated on April 6th, 2020 and the overall number of COVID-19 confirmed cases, total number of hospitalizations and death rates were most recently updated on April 8th, 2020 at 5:00 pm. The overall number of deaths on a daily basis starting March 8th is shown in Figure 1
. The total number of cases in NYC and the COVID-19 mortality rates were also divided based on the five different boroughs of NYC (Figure 2
). Adult obesity rates of the different boroughs were obtained from NYC Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, Community Health Survey 2015-2016 (Figure 3
).

Age adjusted mortality rates for the different ethnic groups in NYC were derived from the Bureau of Communicable Disease Surveillance System as of April 6th, 2020 and were reported based on ethnicity (Figure 4
). Obesity and overweight data divided per ethnicity was obtained from NYC Bureau of Chronic Disease Evaluation and Research which released its obesity data in 2012. Data was collected between 2000 and 2010 as part of the Healthy People 2010 (HP 2010) project (Figure 5
).
